                    <comment id="12566768" author="rolandw" created="Thu, 7 Feb 2008 20:08:49 +0000"  >The only (a)wait is in WaitingThread, the spurious wakeups are handled in ConnPoolByRoute. I&amp;#39;ve implemented a testcase, and the Clover counts indicated that I even caught one real spurious wakeup in addition to the simulated ones :-)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
For the curious: in ConnPoolByRoute.getEntry(...) is the following code block:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
if (waitingThread == null) {&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;waitingThread =&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;newWaitingThread(poolLock.newCondition(), rospl);&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The condition is &amp;#39;false&amp;#39; only if a spurious wakeup is being handled. The testcase generates three simulated ones. If the count indicates that the block has been skipped more often, you know that a real spurious wakeup has occurred.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
cheers,&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Roland&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
